<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[52746]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[The kings of ‘Metamorphosis’]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>Exhibition.</strong> The CCCB presents the work of four important names from the world of animated cinema: Ladislas Starewitch, Jan Švankmajer and the Quay twins.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>Eccentric universes of innocence, cruelty and madness. This is the disturbing environment offered by the work of three big names from the world of animated cinema, who currently have a joint exhibition at the CCCB. Metamorphosis brings together the work of Polish artist Ladislas Starewitch (1882-1965), the Czech master Jan Švankmajer (1934) and the Quay twins (1947).</p>
<p>The exhibition is complemented by a series of screenings and activities, the official catalogue and recommended reading. Don&#8217;t miss out on a journey through this obscure world!</p>
